      "modality": "text",
      "content": "In quadrangular pyramid P-ABCD, base ABCD is a rhombus with angle BAD=60 degrees and AB=2. PA=1 and PA is perpendicular to plane ABCD. Point E is the midpoint of PC and point F is the midpoint of AB. Find the acute dihedral angle between plane PAB and plane PCD. Answer format requirement: <expr>. Strictly forbidden: any extra text beyond this format."
